race.comment: CALL ME MAGNIFIQUE (8) has had his chance in a couple of longer races at Warwick Farm of late but just been found wanting in that company. Rock hard fit and with just 56.5kgs back in a provincial BM68 looks well in. JUST SHANE (4) races beyond 1675m for the first time. Worked home well but lacked the turn of foot required over 1500m at this track last time. The trip is obviously a question mark but he is honest and looks a little one-paced now. ZIGGY ROSE (9) made it two wins from her last three runs when she came with a well-timed run from last to just get home over this distance at Canberra recently. Thriving this prep and although up in grade can win again. Last start Bathurst winner DEVIL RIDER (6) is up in class but we know he'll run the trip.
